        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 1 at 8:11PM EDT until July 1 at 8:30PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 811 PM EDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 13 miles west of Lincolnton to 8 miles northeast of
Gaffney, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and power lines.

Locations impacted include...
Shelby, Lincolnton, Kings Mountain, Cherryville, Bessemer City, South
Gastonia, Blacksburg, Belwood, Grover, and Lawndale.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Move indoors immediately. Lightning is one of nature's leading
killers. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are close enough to
be struck by lightning.</instruction>
